  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p><em>Released 08/29/2022 at 11:30pm CT</em></p><h3 id=\"id-1.18.10-Improvements\">Improvements</h3><ul><li><p>Users can now enable and disable an Open Item List (found under <strong>Company Settings \u2192 Tickets \u2192 General Settings</strong>) which toggles the list of open tickets and appointments a customer has open when adding them to a new ticket.</p></li><li><p>Broadened the ticket statuses that Appointment Reminders can be sent out from to include &quot;Technician Assigned&quot;, &quot;Accepted&quot;, and &quot;Rejected&quot; statuses.</p></li></ul><h3 id=\"id-1.18.10-BugFixes\">Bug Fixes</h3><ul><li><p>Resolved an issue where trying to create any ticket type would sometimes return an error preventing progression.</p></li><li><p>The ticket balance and customer balance, which had been previously calculating incorrectly in automated notifications, now display as intended.</p></li><li><p>Fixed the Appointment Summary &quot;Start&quot; button, which previously did not display any text.</p></li><li><p>Square terminals no longer allow transactions when the integration is turned off.</p></li><li><p>Resolved an issue where RepairQ was calculating a customer's available credit incorrectly after a store credit transaction was removed from a ticket.</p></li><li><p>Return repairs now show custom forms when saved.</p></li></ul>",
      "representation": "export_view",
